<task id="150" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7">
  <metadata>
    <title>Gap A — Naming convention normalization at BFF boundary (sprk_matter → matter) per audit 120</title>
    <phase>Wave 12 — MVP Completion</phase>
    <wave>12</wave>
    <sub-wave>12.4</sub-wave>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>bff-api + code-impl modifying .cs files; affects 5 BFF surfaces (matter-memory, RAG filter, system prompt enrichment, etc.)</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>W12-4</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <tags>bff-api, code-impl, assistant, normalization, wave12</tags>
    <estimated-effort>1-2 days</estimated-effort>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
Audit 120 identified Gap A as the most-impactful single fix for Assistant↔Workspace: SpaarkeAi client sends raw `sprk_matter`; BFF system-prompt enrichment + matter-memory + RAG filter expect normalized `matter`. Five BFF surfaces fragmented across two conventions. Normalize at BFF boundary (smallest blast radius) — accept either form on inbound, internally canonicalize to one convention, propagate that throughout.
  </prompt>

  <role>
You are a BFF developer applying a single boundary-normalization fix that resolves 5 fragmented downstream usages. Surgical edit; preserve all 5 consumer code paths' semantics.
  </role>

  <goal>
Assistant chat in workspace context with matter scope renders matter-aware responses. Specifically: system prompt enrichment is no longer guarded out by name-convention mismatch; matter-memory lookups succeed; RAG filter returns matter-scoped hits. Scenario A from audit 120 ("what matter am I in?") returns matter awareness.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    - Audit notes: projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/audits/wave12-120-assistant-workspace.md (PRIMARY)
    - Top finding: 5 BFF surfaces use two conventions (raw `sprk_matter` vs normalized `matter`)
    - Recommended fix: normalize at BFF boundary (smallest blast radius)
    - Affected files documented in audit (file:line throughout)
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    - Per CLAUDE.md §10: BFF Hygiene checklist; publish-size impact (expect no material change)
    - Per CLAUDE.md §11: modification of existing surfaces; no new abstractions
    - Per ADR-038: integration-heavy tests; ban Mock&lt;HttpMessageHandler&gt; etc.
    - MUST preserve backward compatibility — clients may send either convention; BFF normalizes both
    - MUST NOT change client-side code as part of this task (boundary normalization on the BFF only); client-side changes are out of scope (different convention preserved)
    - Single normalization point: typically a request DTO middleware or service-layer normalization helper
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      - projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/audits/wave12-120-assistant-workspace.md (PRIMARY — Gap A + 5-surface inventory)
      - projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/notes/wave12-mvp-completion-plan.md (§2.3)
      - projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r7/CLAUDE.md
      - .claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md
      - .claude/adr/ADR-038-testing-strategy.md
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <relevant-files>
      - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookChatContextProvider.cs (system prompt enrichment + matter memory)
      - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/** RAG filter / DocumentSearchTools
      - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/Ai/ChatEndpoints.cs (potential normalization boundary)
      - src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/** (chat session shape)
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <steps>
1. **Re-read audit 120 §5 disposition table** (15 min) — confirm full list of 5 surfaces + the normalization-point recommendation
2. **Identify single normalization boundary** (30 min):
   - Likely a service-layer helper called once per request as `NormalizeEntityName(input) → canonical form`
   - OR a request DTO middleware
   - Pick the smallest-blast-radius point
3. **Implement normalization** (60-90 min):
   - Add normalization helper (single method, ~10 LOC)
   - Apply at boundary (the single point identified)
   - Propagate canonical form to all 5 downstream usages (audit 120 lists them)
4. **Add unit tests** (60 min) per ADR-038:
   - Test: raw `sprk_matter` input → canonical output
   - Test: already-canonical input → unchanged
   - Test: unknown entity → graceful handling
5. **Build + test verification** (15 min)
6. **Publish-size impact report** (10 min): verify no material change vs prior R7 baseline ~47 MB

  </steps>

  <tools>
    - Read / Grep / Glob
    - Edit (BFF normalization point + helper)
    - Bash (dotnet test, dotnet build, dotnet publish)
    - TodoWrite
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    - Normalization helper (NEW small file or method) — explicitly justified per CLAUDE.md §11 below
    - 5 downstream surfaces consume canonical form
    - Unit tests covering normalization
    - Publish-size report
  </outputs>

  <justification>
    <existing>No existing single-point normalization helper for entity names; 5 BFF surfaces each handle raw `sprk_matter` differently (audit 120 lists them with file:line)</existing>
    <extension>No — extending each of 5 surfaces independently is the anti-pattern that created this Gap. Single normalization point IS the fix.</extension>
    <cost-of-doing-nothing>Concrete contract failure: `PlaybookChatContextProvider.cs:550` guard expression fails because raw `sprk_matter` doesn't match expected normalized `matter`; system prompt enrichment is unconditionally guarded out; Scenario A ("what matter am I in?") returns no matter awareness. Operator-verified failure in audit 120.</cost-of-doing-nothing>
  </justification>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    - [ ] Single normalization point implemented at BFF boundary
    - [ ] All 5 audit-identified surfaces consume canonical form
    - [ ] Unit tests cover normalization (raw → canonical; canonical → unchanged; unknown → graceful)
    - [ ] `dotnet test` 0 new failures
    - [ ] `dotnet build` 0 errors
    - [ ] Publish-size diff reported
    - [ ] Backward compatibility preserved (clients may send either convention)
    - [ ] Client-side code unchanged
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
